{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:00:33.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 312, "tokens_out": 375, "elapsed_ms": 36439, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a complete 4-page website for a fictional design agency called \"Forma Studio\". The pages are: Home, About, Work (portfolio grid), and Contact. Each page must be a separate HTML file sharing one style.css and one app.js.\n\nWork can be done in parallel across pages, but all pages must share the same visual language: color palette, typography, spacing, component styles. The design system must be defined first and respected by all page builders.\n\nDeliver: home.html, about.html, work.html, contact.html, style.css, app.js, and a report.md explaining design decisions and how consistency was maintained across parallel work.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:00:58.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1282, "tokens_out": 976, "elapsed_ms": 25135, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"design-system\",\n      \"description\": \"Define the design system including color palette, typography, spacing, and component styles. Produce style.css with global styles and app.js with shared functionality. Document decisions in report.md.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"home-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create home.html as the main entry page. Include a hero section, featured work preview, and navigation to about.html, work.html, and contact.html. Must use styles from style.css and link to app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"about-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create about.html with an agency story section, team introduction, and values. Include navigation links to home.html, work.html, and contact.html. Must follow the shared style.css and app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"work-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create work.html displaying a responsive portfolio grid of at least 6 projects. Each project includes title, image, and category. Include navigation to home.html, about.html, and contact.html. Must use style.css and app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"contact-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create contact.html with a contact form (name, email, message), studio address, and social links. Include navigation to home.html, about.html, and work.html. Must follow the shared style.css and app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integration-test\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify all pages (home.html, about.html, work.html, contact.html) share consistent visual language and functionality. Ensure index.html exists (as home.html) and all pages are linked. Finalize report.md with consistency audit and design rationale.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
